{
  "stem": "18575.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The first tanks were hit with Molotov cocktails and with-- with grenades.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And all we saw is fire coming out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We didn't see the tanks.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were blocked by-- by buildings.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There were-- also, we heard machine gun fire from the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "By the way, that's only one machine gun.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "That's all we had, one machine gun.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "If [? wachta ?] ever talked to you, the Polish Underground, the AK, Armia Krajowa, the National Polish Underground Army, which was well-equipped with weapons left from the war that they hid Polish weapons from the-- from the war would not give or sell the weapons to the Jews.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They say it's waste.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The weapons were bought on a black market.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And a Leftist underground Polish called AL, Armia Ludowa, People's Army, sold and gave some hand weapons, carbines, and pistols, and a few grenades.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So there was very little of-- of defense, mostly molotov, mostly bombs made in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Because they smuggled in chemicals, phosphor and others, and made bombs.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, I had no input to it at all.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that's how it started.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was for no more than a week, maybe eight days, where we acted as couriers.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then, the group that we were working with moved out, further out.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We couldn't be in touch with them, because the Germans were burning building by building, and attacking it, and gaining control.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the fighting was going on continuously.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was weapons that we captured from Germans that were killed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Also, there were factories making uniform for the German army.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Some of those uniforms were stolen, and the-- and the fighters put on the uniforms and got down to the-- down to the streets, shot some Germans, got their weapons.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
